        "chunk_text": "[MNO: VZW | Release: 2026_feb | Plan: Reqs-LTE_OTADM | Version: 46]\n[Path: OTA-DM SPECIFICATIONS > COMMON REQUIREMENTS FOR OTADM - STANDARDS > DM CONNECTIVITY REQUIREMENTS > NETWORK INITIATED DM SESSIONS]\n[Req ID: VZ_REQ_LTEOTADM_22986]\n\nNETWORK INITIATED DM SESSIONS\n1.5.1.4.1.1DM Notification via SMS message (Trigger)\nOTADM compliant devices shall receive and process Device Management notifications delivered to the device  via an SMS message.\nNOTE: SMS messages are configured and sent by the OTADM Server over the IMS PDN. Network-Initiated  functionality is triggered by these SMS.\n1.5.1.4.1.23GPP and 3GPP2 SMS Format Support\n1.5.1.4.1.3LTE Service Required\n1.5.1.4.1.4Network Initiated (NI) Retry\nIf the device is in adequate LTE coverage area, but the network-initiated DM session fails to connect  to the server for any reason, the device shall fail the session and not retry.\n[Table: VZ_REQ_LTEOTADM_4105999311951449]\n[Table: VZ_REQ_LTEOTADM_7674]\n[Image: 1.5.1.4.1.3LTE Service Required VZ_REQ_LTEOTADM_7674]",
