        "chunk_text": "[MNO: VZW | Release: 2026_feb | Plan: Reqs-LTE_OTADM | Version: 46]\n[Path: OTA-DM SPECIFICATIONS > COMMON REQUIREMENTS FOR OTADM - STANDARDS > OTADM TRANSPORT SECURITY REQUIREMENTS > Support for MSISDN]\n[Req ID: VZ_REQ_LTEOTADM_5965085]\n\nSupport for MSISDN\nThe device shall support a MSISDN which may be up to 15 digits long. If the assigned MSISDN is 11  digits long with the leading digit of 1 (e.g., 15551234567), then the least significant 10 digits shall be  used. Otherwise, full MSISDN shall be used (e.g., 9991234567890, 35312345678).  Additionally, for devices using a pMSISDN (pseudo MSISDN) shall be defined with 13 digits and  always start with 999 for the Country Code. As an example, this may be used for devices in a private  network environment that do not support a traditional MSISDN.\n[Image: VZ_REQ_LTEOTADM_4105999311951848 The device shall support a MSISDN which may be up to 15 digits long. If the assigned MSISDN is 11  digits long with the leading digit of 1 (e.g., 15551234567), then the least significant 10 digits sha]",
        "chunk_length_chars": 1045,
